questions.question:
Consider the following code and trace the execution flow:
try {
 try {
 int[] arr = new int[5];
 arr[10] = 100;
 } catch (ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException e) {
 System.out.println("Inner: Array index issue");
 throw new RuntimeException("Runtime error occurred");
 } finally {
 System.out.println("Inner finally executed");
 }
} catch (RuntimeException e) {
 System.out.println("Outer: " + e.getMessage());
} finally {
 System.out.println("Outer finally executed");
}

Analyze the output and explain the exception propagation mechanism.
